-# The Detail column carries the change_type category ("Metadata" vs
-# "Permissions") + a payload summary (changed fields, or the before→after ACL
-# diff), so the bare `update` verb is no longer ambiguous.
-#
-# TODO (Permission History): make the `permissions` category label (see
-# audit_event_change_type_badge) a hyperlink to a per-resource Permission
-# History view — the v2 successor to v1's "Rights History" diff page. Now
-# feasible because Atlas 0.6.40 records `payload: { before:, after: }` on every
-# permissions event. Design note:
-# ~/projects/gap_reports/atlas_audit_permission_history_view.md
%tr.audit-event.audit-event--update
  %td= audit_event_timestamp(event)
  %td= audit_event_action_badge(event)
  %td.audit-event__detail-cell= audit_event_detail_cell(event)
  %td= audit_event_who(event)
